  "text": "Kubernetes RBAC privilege escalation prevention is implemented through a multi-layered validation system. The core escalation check logic is in `pkg/registry/rbac/escalation_check.go`, which provides three key functions: `EscalationAllowed()` checks if a user is in the system:masters group (superusers), `RoleEscalationAuthorized()` explicitly checks if a user has the 'escalate' verb on the role resource being modified, and `BindingAuthorized()` checks if a user can bind a specific role.\n\nThe main escalation prevention logic resides in `pkg/registry/rbac/validation/rule.go`. The `ConfirmNoEscalation()` function compares the rules a user is trying to create with their own permissions using the `Covers()` function from `staging/src/k8s.io/component-helpers/auth/rbac/validation/policy_comparator.go`. This ensures users cannot grant themselves permissions they don't already possess. The `DefaultRuleResolver` class resolves the complete set of permissions a user has from both ClusterRoles and Roles across all relevant bindings.\n\nAll four RBAC resource storage layers enforce these checks: `pkg/registry/rbac/clusterrole/policybased/storage.go` and `pkg/registry/rbac/role/policybased/storage.go` validate rules directly through `ConfirmNoEscalationInternal()`, while `pkg/registry/rbac/clusterrolebinding/policybased/storage.go` and `pkg/registry/rbac/rolebinding/policybased/storage.go` validate the permissions contained in the referenced role.\n\nThe 'escalate' verb is defined in `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/controller_policy.go` and is part of the standard RBAC authorization enforcement implemented by `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go`. The verb matching and rule evaluation is performed through helper functions in `pkg/apis/rbac/v1/evaluation_helpers.go`. Rule comparison is optimized using `pkg/registry/rbac/validation/policy_compact.go` which consolidates simple rules for clearer error messages when escalation is denied."
}

